<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="186" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,151,429]" pageId="35" pageNumber="186">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,260,285]" pageId="35" pageNumber="186">Remarks.</emphasis>
The long pubescence, particularly on the head, and the presence of the ridge on the mesosternal collar will quickly distinguish this species from all others except 
<taxonomicName box="[911,983,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Ptiliidae" genus="Acrotrichis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bibula">
<emphasis box="[911,983,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="186">bibula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which it may be separated by its narrower shape and the form of the spermatheca.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
